Theming utilities for your Neovim.
STATUS: WIP
NVIM: v0.9.0-dev

PACKER
------
Following is a very minimal configuration for colo.
Plenary is the only hard-dependency. You can opt-out
installing integration plugins if you decide not to use
colo integrations or, prefer your own configuration instead.
use({
  "dharmx/nvim-colo",
  requires = {
    "nvim-lua/plenary.nvim",
    "akinsho/bufferline.nvim",
    "feline-nvim/feline.nvim",
    {
      "lewis6991/gitsigns.nvim", ---required by feline
      config = function()
        require("gitsigns").setup()
      end
    },
    "kyazdani42/nvim-web-devicons",
  },
  config = function()
    ---integrations are enabled by default
    require("colo").setup()
  end
})

CONFIG
______
Configuration is done by passing a table to the setup function.
The following is the default configuration.
local config = {
  theme = "radium", ---only nvim-colo themes are allowed
  variant = "dark",
  integrations = {
    feline = true,
    bufferline = true,
    devicons = true,
  },
}

COMMANDS
--------
:Colo <theme_name>

